    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "6dbbad28a7cf72e1",
      "text": "It was essential to the performance that the videos were blown up from the tiny poster size videos that we found on the internet and projected at a cinematic scale, with high quality ambient audio tracks. The work was as much an audio performance as a video installation.  The audience was then invited to discuss the work. \n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "812535261b1cfaa7",
      "text": "Interestingly the audience was unusually mute, which was most likely due to the hypnotic effect of the cyclic video, and the immersive nature of the projection which left you feeling virtually sea-sick. We never got to the discussion we sought."
    },
